79710>>>>>// Courtesy Of Vincent Oorsprong
79710>>>>>// This function formats the time in a picture-string passed
79710>>>>>//
79710>>>>>// Picture      Meaning
79710>>>>>//    h         Hours with no leading zero for single-digit hours; 12-hour clock
79710>>>>>//    hh        Hours with leading zero for single-digit hours; 12-hour clock
79710>>>>>//    H         Hours with no leading zero for single-digit hours; 24-hour clock
79710>>>>>//    HH        Hours with leading zero for single-digit hours; 24-hour clock
79710>>>>>//    m         Minutes with no leading zero for single-digit minutes
79710>>>>>//    mm        Minutes with leading zero for single-digit minutes
79710>>>>>//    s         Seconds with no leading zero for single-digit seconds
79710>>>>>//    ss        Seconds with leading zero for single-digit seconds
79710>>>>>//    t         One character time marker string, such as A or P
79710>>>>>//    tt        Multicharacter time marker string, such as AM or PM
79710>>>>>//
79710>>>>>// For example, to get the time string  "11:29:40 PM"
79710>>>>>//    use the following picture string: "hh" : "mm" : "ss tt"
79710>>>>>
79710>>>>>External_function vWin32_GetTimeFormat "GetTimeFormatA" Kernel32.Dll ;  Dword LCID Dword dwFlags Pointer lpsSystemTime Pointer lpFormat Pointer lpTimeStr ;  Integer cchTime Returns Integer
79711>>>>>
79711>>>>>
79711>>>>>// Courtesy Of Vincent Oorsprong
79711>>>>>// This function formats the date in a picture-string passed
79711>>>>>//
79711>>>>>// Picture      Meaning
79711>>>>>//    d         Day of month as digits with no leading zero for single-digit days.
79711>>>>>//    dd        Day of month as digits with leading zero for single-digit days.
79711>>>>>//    ddd       Day of week as a three-letter abbreviation. The function uses the
79711>>>>>//              LOCALE_SABBREVOAYMAME value associated with the specified locale.
79711>>>>>//    dddd      Day of week as its full name. The function uses the LOCALE_SDAYNAME
79711>>>>>//              value associated with the specified locale.
79711>>>>>//    M         Month as digits with no leading zero for single-digit months.
79711>>>>>//    MM        Month as digits with leading zero for single-digit months.
79711>>>>>//    MMM       Month as a three-letter abbreviation. The function uses the
79711>>>>>//              LOCALE_SABBREVMONTHNAME value associated with the specified locale.
79711>>>>>//    MMMM      Month as its full name. The function uses the LOCALE_SMONTHNAME value
79711>>>>>//              associated with the specified locale.
79711>>>>>//    y         Year as last two digits, but with no leading zero for years less than 10.
79711>>>>>//    yy        Year as last two digits, but with leading zero for years less than 10.
79711>>>>>//    yyyy      Year represented hy full four digits.
79711>>>>>//    gg        Period/era string. The function uses the CAL_SERASTRING value associated
79711>>>>>//              with the specified locale. This element is ignored if the date to be formatted
79711>>>>>//              does not have an associated era or period string.
79711>>>>>// For example, to get the date string  "Wed, Aug 31 94"
79711>>>>>// use the following picture string:    "ddd","MMM dd yy"
79711>>>>>
79711>>>>>External_function vWin32_GetDateFormat "GetDateFormatA" Kernel32.Dll ;  Dword LCID Dword dwFlags Pointer lpsSystemTime Pointer lpFormat Pointer lpDateStr ;  Integer cchDate Returns Integer
