81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_OEM_TRANSLATION
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description There are two sets of code pages used in windows, ANSI and
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// OEM. ANSI is what is commonly used now, but some data still uses the OEM
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// code pages. When migrating data, this attribute is used to determine whether
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// the OEM data will be translated to ANSI during the migration. For example,
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// migrating passwords with special characters may call for different code pages.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Setting this attribute to true will convert the OEM data to ANSI, setting it
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// to false will not.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-08-15 by Aaron Gulack
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @INTOPT
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Set_Attribute DF_FILE_OEM_TRANSLATION of {FileNumber} to {variable}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Get_Attribute DF_FILE_OEM_TRANSLATION of {FileNumber} to {variable}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber            Number of the file
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable              Indicates if OEM data will be converted to ANSI. True converts it, false does not.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// open Customer
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Handle hFile
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Boolean bTranslate
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Move Customer.File_Number to hFile
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Structure_Start hFile
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///     Set_Attribute DF_FILE_OEM_TRANSLATION of hFile to True
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///     Get_Attribute DF_FILE_OEM_TRANSLATION of hFile to bTranslate
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Structure_End hFile
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>Define DF_FILE_OEM_TRANSLATION                      For (DF_FILE_RECORD_REREAD+51)
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_EPOCH_YEAR
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description When dealing with two-digit years, an epoch year must be used
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// to determine which century the date is referring to. For example if the
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// epoch year is set to 30, then any two digit year greater than 30 will be
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// considered in the 20th Century, anything less than or equal to 30 will be
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// considered in the 21st Century.  This attribute is used to turn on or off
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// this feature. To use this feature, set this attribute to whatever the epoch
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// year is expected to be. To disable this feature, set this attribute to 0
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// or false. Note that setting this attribute must be done at table creation
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// or inside of a Structure_Start.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-08-15 by Aaron Gulack
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @INTOPT      EPOCH_YEAR
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Set_Attribute DF_FILE_EPOCH_YEAR of {FileNumber} to {variable}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Get_Attribute DF_FILE_EPOCH_YEAR of {FileNumber} to {variable}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber            Number of the file
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable              Indicates what the epoch year is. 0 to disable
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// open Customer
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Handle hFile
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Boolean bEpoch
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Move Customer.File_Number to hFile
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Structure_Start hFile
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///     Set_Attribute DF_FILE_EPOCH_YEAR of hFile to 30
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///     Get_Attribute DF_FILE_EPOCH_YEAR of hFile to bEpoch
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Structure_End hFile
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>Define DF_FILE_EPOCH_YEAR                           For (DF_FILE_RECORD_REREAD+53)
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>Define DF_FILE_USE_ROWCOUNT_IN_TRANSACTIONS         For 628
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>Define DF_FILE_ICF_STATUS                           For 630
