81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_LOCK_RECORD_STATUS
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description Table locking is done during transactions to maintain atomicity.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// In DataFlex, this is usually done with the REREAD/UNLOCK commands. This
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// attribute is used to get the status of a table lock. If a table is currently
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// in a REREAD, or locked, then the attribute will return true. Otherwise, it
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// returns false. It is a read-only attribute so no setting can be done.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-08-06 by Aaron Gulack
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @INTOPT
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Get_Attribute DF_FILE_LOCK_RECORD_STATUS of {FileNumber} to {variable}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber            Number of the file
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable              Indicates the status of the file lock
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// open Customer
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Handle hFile
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Integer bLocked
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Move Customer.File_Number to hFile
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Get_Attribute DF_FILE_LOCK_RECORD_STATUS of hFile to bLocked
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>Define DF_FILE_LOCK_RECORD_STATUS                   For 632
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_CASING
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description Controls the filename and column name casing.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// You can set this to either keep the file case, force to lower case or force
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// to uppercase.
