81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_RECNUM_TABLE
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description Dataflex's embedded database, by default, uses a Recnum column
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// as the unique identifier for a table instead of a primary key. A table can
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// easily be changed to use another column though and this attribute gets or
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// sets whether the Recnum is being used for a table. Getting the value of this
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// attribute can be done at any time for any driver. The setting of this attribute,
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// however, can only be done in certain situations. Only if an alternative primary
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// key is set up already can this attribute be set to false and only during a
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Structure_Start. Also, the attribute can only be turned off (set to false),
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// it can not be turned back on (set to True).
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Note: In Postgres, this attribute is a ReadOnly attribute and can not be set.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public (PGFlex ReadOnly)
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-08-12 by Aaron Gulack
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See                 DF_FILE_RECNUM_NAME DF_FILE_PRIMARY_INDEX
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @INTOPT
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Get_Attribute DF_FILE_RECNUM_TABLE of {FileNumber} to {variable}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Set_Attribute DF_FILE_RECNUM_TABLE of {FileNumber} to {variable}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber            Number of the file
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable              Boolean variable indicating if recnum is used
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Open Customer
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Boolean bRecnum
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Handle hFile
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Move Customer.File_Number to hFile
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Structure_Start hFile
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///     Set_Attribute DF_FILE_RECNUM_TABLE of Customer.File_Number to False
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///     Get_Attribute DF_FILE_RECNUM_TABLE of Customer.File_Number to bRecnum
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Structure_End hFile
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>Define DF_FILE_RECNUM_TABLE                         For 1401
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_PRIMARY_INDEX
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description This attribute gets or sets the index which is used as the
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// primary key for a table. The variable used for this attribute is an integer
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// containing the numbered index used. Getting the value of this attribute can
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// be done at any time, whereas setting can only be done at table creation or
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// during a Structure_Start. If a RECNUM is used as the unique identifier then
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// 0 is returned.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Note: In Postgres this attribute is ReadOnly, so it can only be used to get
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// the index used as the primary key.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public (PGFlex ReadOnly)
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-08-12 by Aaron Gulack
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See                 DF_FILE_RECNUM_NAME
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @INTOPT
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Get_Attribute DF_FILE_PRIMARY_INDEX of {FileNumber} to {variable}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Set_Attribute DF_FILE_PRIMARY_INDEX of {FileNumber} to {variable}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber            Number of the file
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable              Boolean variable indicating if a primary key is used
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Open Customer
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Boolean bPrimary
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Handle hFile
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
