81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>//Comment Block Template
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>//======================
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name {Name of the command for indexing} (used for documentation)
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description {Short Command Description} (used for documentation)
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>///     The description can be multiple lines, and contain HTML tags.
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>///     The other tokens will have HTML encoded so we can show stuff
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>///     like <param1> properly. A blank line will automatically be
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>///         translated into a paragraph break in the documentation, so
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>///     no need for <br> or <p> tags.
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions {Assumptions made in order for the command to work}
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status {Obsolete, Internal, or Public} (used for documentation)
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers {DB2Flex, MySQLFlex, ORAFlex, PgFlex, SQLFlex or All} (used for documentation)
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote {Date and author of the last revision}
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See {list of related commands}
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax {Syntax of use} (used for documentation)
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param {Each parameter with a brief description} (used for documentation)
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @DBMS {List of supported databases}
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @DataFlex {List of supported DataFlex versions}
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Usage {Different uses command can have multiple syntaxes} (used for documentation)
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example {An example of the command being used} (used for documentation)
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        DO_GETFILENUMBER_DRIVERNAME
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description Retrieves the current driver name and or the file number
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// that will be used by the macro commands.
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Internal Use Only
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2009-07-14 By Ian Smith
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>//Most commands use DO_GETFILENUMBER_DRIVERNAME so this code was being duplicated
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>//all the time. It has been moved to this method to remove that duplication.
81361>>>>>>>>>>>>>Procedure MertechInc_Get_Driver_name Global
81363>>>>>>>>>>>>>    //If we have a file number get its driver, else find first loaded Mertech driver
81363>>>>>>>>>>>>>    If MertechInc_FileNumber GT 0 ;        Get_Attribute DF_FILE_DRIVER of MertechInc_FileNumber to MertechInc_DriverName
81368>>>>>>>>>>>>>    Else Begin
81369>>>>>>>>>>>>>        If (MertechInc_CurrentDriver > "") Move MertechInc_CurrentDriver to MertechInc_DriverName
81372>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Else Begin
81373>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Get_Attribute DF_NUMBER_DRIVERS to MertechInc_iCount
81376>>>>>>>>>>>>>            For MertechInc_iLoop from 1 to MertechInc_iCount
81382>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81382>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_NAME of MertechInc_iLoop to MertechInc_DriverName
81385>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Move (UPPERCASE(MertechInc_DriverName)) to MertechInc_DriverName
81386>>>>>>>>>>>>>                If (MertechInc_DriverName EQ ORAFLEX  or MertechInc_DriverName EQ SQLFLEX or MertechInc_DriverName EQ MDSDB2 or ;                    MertechInc_DriverName EQ MDSPgSQL or MertechInc_DriverName EQ MDSMySQL) Move MertechInc_iCount to MertechInc_iLoop
81389>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Else Move "" to MertechInc_DriverName
81391>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Loop
81392>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81392>>>>>>>>>>>>>        End
81392>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81392>>>>>>>>>>>>>    End
81392>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81392>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81392>>>>>>>>>>>>>    //Ensure that we return a valid Mertech driver.
81392>>>>>>>>>>>>>    If (MertechInc_DriverName NE ORAFLEX  and ;        MertechInc_DriverName NE SQLFLEX  and ;        MertechInc_DriverName NE MDSDB2   and ;        MertechInc_DriverName NE MDSPgSQL and ;        MertechInc_DriverName NE MDSMySQL     ) ;        Begin
81394>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81394>>>>>>>>>>>>>        //Report invalid driver
81394>>>>>>>>>>>>>//        Error 25100 ("Invalid Driver - file" * String(MertechInc_FileNumber))
81394>>>>>>>>>>>>>//        Error 25100 ("Mertech.inc - Not a Mertech driver (file number " * String(MertechInc_FileNumber) * ")")
81394>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Error 25100 ("Mertech.inc - Not a Mertech driver. File" * String(MertechInc_FileNumber) * "Driver" * Trim(MertechInc_DriverName) )
81395>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81395>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81395>>>>>>>>>>>>>        //Set MertechInc_FileNumber to MertechInc_Invalid_Driver so that the commands can
81395>>>>>>>>>>>>>        //determine if the driver is valid. MertechInc_FileNumber is use instead of
81395>>>>>>>>>>>>>        //MertechInc_DriverName as integer conparisons are quicker than string conparisons
81395>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Move MertechInc_Invalid_Driver to MertechInc_FileNumber
81396>>>>>>>>>>>>>    End
81396>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81396>>>>>>>>>>>>>End_Procedure
81397>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81397>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
81397>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        MertechInc_Pre_Size_String
81397>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description Returns a string full of spaces.
81397>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81397>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
81397>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Internal
81397>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     n/a
81397>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2009-12-02 By Gandalf Hernandez
81397>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See
81397>>>>>>>>>>>>>Function MertechInc_Pre_Size_String Global Integer iSize Returns String
81399>>>>>>>>>>>>>   Local String sWork
81399>>>>>>>>>>>>>   Local Integer iBlocks iRemainder
81399>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81399>>>>>>>>>>>>>   If (iSize <= 1) Begin
81401>>>>>>>>>>>>>      // marcelo 06/28/2000 implemented logic to avoid VDF 7 crashing problems
81401>>>>>>>>>>>>>          If FMAC_VERSION eq 7 Move 1000 to iSize
81404>>>>>>>>>>>>>          Else Move 16384 to iSize
81406>>>>>>>>>>>>>   End
81406>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81406>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81406>>>>>>>>>>>>>   // Build the string in blocks of 32, to speed things up
81406>>>>>>>>>>>>>   // If the string is less than 32 bytes, just fill it up regularly
81406>>>>>>>>>>>>>   Move (iSize / 32) to iBlocks
81407>>>>>>>>>>>>>   Move (Mod(iSize, 32)) to iRemainder
81408>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81408>>>>>>>>>>>>>   If (iBlocks > 0) Begin
81410>>>>>>>>>>>>>      Move (Repeat("                                ", iBlocks)) to sWork
81411>>>>>>>>>>>>>      Move (Append (sWork, (Repeat(" ", iRemainder)))) to sWork
81412>>>>>>>>>>>>>   End
81412>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81412>>>>>>>>>>>>>   Else Move (Repeat(" ", iSize)) to sWork
81414>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81414>>>>>>>>>>>>>   Function_Return sWork
81415>>>>>>>>>>>>>End_Function
81416>>>>>>>>>>>>>
