81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        FETCH_FIELD
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description Selects or de-selects the fields to be fetched during the
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// next FIND (query).
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Internal
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2009-07-16 By Ian Smith
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax FETCH_FIELD <FileNum> <FieldStart> THRU <FieldEnd> TO DF_FETCH_TRUE
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNum    is the File Number
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FieldStart is the Field Name or Number that will start the selection range
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FieldEnd   is the Field Name or Number that will finish the selection range
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax FETCH_FIELD <FileNum> <Field1> TO DF_FETCH_TRUE
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNum  is the File Number
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  Field1 Fields Name or Number to be selected
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        SQL_TEXT_MESSAGE
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description Use this command to manually insert a string into a trace
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// file. This can be useful for readability within the trace file to log
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// what is actually happening at certain points.
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions The text string is less than 80 characters long.
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 20013-08-19 by Aaron Gulack
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See         ENABLE_TRACE_ON DISABLE_TRACE_ON
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax SQL_TEXT_MESSAGE {variable}
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  {variable}          The string to insert into the trace file.
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Login "localhost" "mds" "mertech" "ora_drv"
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// ENABLE_TRACE_ON to "c:\trace.txt" DEBUG_LEVEL
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// open Customer
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// SQL_TEXT_MESSAGE "The table has been opened"
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name       SELECT_COLUMNS_FIND
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description This command is used to fetch only a certain number of fields
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// while doing a "find". When specifying the field number to start from and
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// field number to end on, the find will only fetch the given fields from the
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// record. It is important to always use this command after first deselecting
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// all columns i.e. setting RESET_FETCH_FIELDS to DF_FETCH_FALSE. Also, after
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// using this command, all columns need to be reselected i.e. setting
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// RESET_FETCH_FIELDS to DF_FETCH_TRUE. Note that fields used as a part the
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// index segment associated with the find will always be fetched regardless.
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 20014-04-30 by Marcello Yo
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See         RESET_FETCH_FIELDS DISABLE_SELECT_COLUMNS_ERRORS
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax SELECT_COLUMNS_FIND {FileNumber} {fieldStart} THRU {fieldEnd}
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber          The number of the file
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  fieldStart          The field number to start the fetch from
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FieldEnd            The field number to end the fetch at
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Open Customer
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// RESET_FETCH_FIELDS  CUSTOMER DF_FETCH_FALSE
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// SELECT_COLUMNS_FIND CUSTOMER CUSTOMER_NUMBER NAME
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// DISABLE_SELECT_COLUMNS_ERRORS DISABLED
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Clear Customer
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Repeat
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///    Find Gt Customer by Index.1
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///    If (Found) Showln Customer.Customer_Number '-' Customer.Name
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Until (Not(Found))
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// RESET_FETCH_FIELDS Customer DF_FETCH_TRUE
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        RESET_FETCH_FIELDS
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description This command is used to specify whether to retrieve all columns
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// or no columns when performing a find. It is usually used with the command
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// SELECT_COLUMNS_FIND to reset the column fetching. This command can either be
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// set to DF_FETCH_TRUE, which will fetch all columns or set to DF_FETCH_FALSE,
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// which will fetch no columns.
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2014-04-30 by Marcello Yo
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See         SELECT_COLUMNS_FIND DISABLE_SELECT_COLUMNS_ERRORS
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax RESET_FETCH_FIELDS {FileNumber} {DF_FETCH_TRUE/DF_FETCH_FALSE}
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber                  The number of the file
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  DF_FETCH_TRUE               fetch all columns
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  DF_FETCH_FALSE              fetch no columns
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Open Customer
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// RESET_FETCH_FIELDS  CUSTOMER DF_FETCH_FALSE
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// SELECT_COLUMNS_FIND CUSTOMER CUSTOMER_NUMBER NAME
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// DISABLE_SELECT_COLUMNS_ERRORS DISABLED
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Clear Customer
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Repeat
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///    Find Gt Customer by Index.1
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///    If (Found) Showln Customer.Customer_Number '-' Customer.Name
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Until (Not(Found))
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// RESET_FETCH_FIELDS Customer DF_FETCH_TRUE
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        SQL_FOR_ONEROW
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description This command will instruct the driver to fetch one row
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// per query
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Deprecated
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-08-19 by Aaron Gulack
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax SQL_FOR_ONEROW {FileNumber}
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber          The number of the file
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///     open Customer
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///     SQL_FOR_ONEROW Customer.File_Number
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///     Repeat
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///             find gt Customer by Recnum
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///         If (Found) Begin
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///             showln "Sales name is " Customer.FirstName
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///         end
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///     until (Customer.ID = 10)
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        SQL_REFRESH_CACHE
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description For optimization during record retrieval, a set number of
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// records are stored in a local cache. This command forces a refresh, by
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// making the next find retrieve the record from the database instead of
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// the cache.
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-08-19 by Aaron Gulack
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax SQL_REFRESH_CACHE OF {FileNumber}
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber          The number of the file
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Open Customer
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Find gt Customer by Index.1
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// While (Found) Begin
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///     showln "Customer name is " CUSTOMER.CUSTOMER
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Loop
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// SQL_REFRESH_CACHE of CUSTOMER
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        SQL_FOR_SET
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description Use this command during LT or GT finds to only fetch a set
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// number of rows. An option is also available for this command to disable
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// the local cash by passing NOCACHE at the end of the command call. Note
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// that if the rowcount is set low, too many round-trips to the server may
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// result, effecting performance significantly. Also, if the rowcount is set
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// too high a large number of records can be pre-fetched and end up not being
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// used by the application. Because of this, the default of 10 rows and a cache
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// will be adequate for most situations.
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-08-20 by Aaron Gulack
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax SQL_FOR_SET {FileNumber} MAXROWS {variable} {CACHE/NOCACHE}
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber          The number of the file
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable            The maximum number of rows to retrieve
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  CACHE               fetched rows will be kept at the local cache
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  NOCACHE             fetched rows will not be kept at the local cache
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Open Customer
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// SQL_FOR_SET Customer MAXROWS 15 CACHE
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// find gt Customer by Index.1
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        SQL_SET
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description Initializes and sets an initial statement for embedded
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// sql execution.
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions Parameter may be more than 255 characters long so redirect to method.
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Deprecated
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-08-20 by Aaron Gulack
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See         SQL_SET_STMT
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax SQL_SET {FileNumber}
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber          The number of the file
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81435>>>>>>>>>>>>>Procedure MertechInc_SQL_SET Global String sStatement
81437>>>>>>>>>>>>>    Call_Driver 0 MertechInc_DriverName Function 1 CALLBACK 0 PASSING MertechInc_Blank sStatement 0 RESULT MertechInc_iRet
81442>>>>>>>>>>>>>End_Procedure
81443>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81443>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
81443>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        SQL_APPEND
81443>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description Appends a string value to the current embedded sql statement
81443>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// already set.
81443>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81443>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions Parameter may be more than 255 characters long so redirect to method.
81443>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Deprecated
81443>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
81443>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-08-20 by Aaron Gulack
81443>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See                 SQL_APPEND_STMT
81443>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81443>>>>>>>>>>>>>Procedure MertechInc_SQL_APPEND Global String sStatement
81445>>>>>>>>>>>>>    Call_Driver 0 MertechInc_DriverName Function 2 CALLBACK 0 PASSING MertechInc_Blank sStatement 0 RESULT MertechInc_iRet
81450>>>>>>>>>>>>>End_Procedure
81451>>>>>>>>>>>>>
