82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_TIME
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description This command is used to find out how long until a
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// specific temporary license for a driver expires. If 0 is returned,
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// then the license is not a temporary license. If -1 is returned, then
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// the license has already expired. Otherwise, the number returned
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// is the number of days until the license will expire.
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-10-02 Aaron Gulack
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See                 GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_PATH SET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_WARNING
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_TIME to {variable}
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param variable                     Variable to hold the days until expiration
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_TIME to iExpire
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Showln iExpire
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        SET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_WARNING
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description This command is used to set a custom warning message to
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// be displayed when a temporary license for a driver is close to expiring.
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Note that since the license evaluation is done during Login and before
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// any open calls, this command should be called before either of those.
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-10-02 by Aaron Gulack
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See                 GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_PATH GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_TIME
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax SET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_WARNING to {variable}
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param variable                     New warning message for expiring license
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// SET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_WARNING to "Your license is about to expire."
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Login "localhost" "" "" "sql_drv"
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_PATH
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description This command will return the current path of the license
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// associated with the driver.
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Internal
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-10-01 by Aaron Gulack
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See                 SET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_WARNING GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_TIME
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_PATH to {variable}
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param variable                     Variable to hold the path of the license
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>
82438>>>>>>>>>>>>>Function MertechInc_GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_PATH Global Returns String
82440>>>>>>>>>>>>>    Local String sReturnValue
82440>>>>>>>>>>>>>
82440>>>>>>>>>>>>>    DO_GETFILENUMBER_DRIVERNAME 0
82442>>>>>>>>>>>>>    If (MertechInc_FileNumber <> -1) Begin
82444>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Get MertechInc_Pre_Size_String 4096 to sReturnValue
82445>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Call_Driver 0 MertechInc_DriverName Function CALLDRV_LICENSE_ENVIRONMENT_SET CALLBACK 0 PASSING sReturnValue MertechInc_Blank CALLDRV_LICENSE_PATH RESULT MertechInc_iRet
82450>>>>>>>>>>>>>        If MertechInc_iRet EQ -1 INDICATE ERR True
82453>>>>>>>>>>>>>    End
82453>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
82453>>>>>>>>>>>>>
82453>>>>>>>>>>>>>    Function_Return sReturnValue
82454>>>>>>>>>>>>>End_Function
