82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// SET_AUTHENTICATION_MODE of Oracle to DEFAULT
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        SQL_ESCAPE_STRING
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description This command is used to properly escape strings before
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// they are used in embedded SQL statements. This can be extremely
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// important when you do not have full control of the strings being passed
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// to the SQL statement as this will ensure that the strings are properly
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// quoted.
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-10-02 by Aaron Gulack
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax SQL_ESCAPE_STRING of {string} to {variable}
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param string               The string to be escaped.
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param variable     Variable to hold the newly escaped string
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// SQL_ESCAPE_STRING of "They said to me, 'hello'." to sEscaped
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>Function SQLESCAPESTRING Global String sData Returns String
82457>>>>>>>>>>>>>    String sReturnData
82457>>>>>>>>>>>>>
82457>>>>>>>>>>>>>    DO_GETFILENUMBER_DRIVERNAME 0
82459>>>>>>>>>>>>>
82459>>>>>>>>>>>>>    If (MertechInc_FileNumber <> -1) Begin
82461>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Get MertechInc_Pre_Size_String 0 to sReturnData
82462>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Call_Driver 0 MertechInc_DriverName Function CALLDRV_ESCAPE_STRING CALLBACK 0 PASSING sData sReturnData 0 RESULT MertechInc_iRet
82467>>>>>>>>>>>>>    End
82467>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
82467>>>>>>>>>>>>>
82467>>>>>>>>>>>>>    Function_Return sReturnData
82468>>>>>>>>>>>>>End_Function
