84803>>>>>>>>>>>    Define EN_DbTypeMSSQL
84803>>>>>>>>>>>    Define EN_DbTypeMySQL
84803>>>>>>>>>>>    Define EN_DbTypeOracle
84803>>>>>>>>>>>    Define EN_DbTypeDB2 
84803>>>>>>>>>>>    Define EN_DbTypePostgre 
84803>>>>>>>>>>>    Define EN_DbTypeDataFlex // Embedded database.
84803>>>>>>>>>>>End_Enum_List 
84803>>>>>>>>>>>
84803>>>>>>>>>>>// We need to have our "own" constants for the standard DataFlex data types.
84803>>>>>>>>>>>// These can be used with SQL functions such as e.g. SQLColumnAdd, instead
84803>>>>>>>>>>>// of using one of the driver specific integer constants such as e.g. "SQL_VARCHAR".
84803>>>>>>>>>>>// We need to re-define the standard constants because several driver constants
84803>>>>>>>>>>>// have the same value and we need to be able to distinguish which data type to use when
84803>>>>>>>>>>>// e.g. creating a column with embedded SQL (ESQL).
84803>>>>>>>>>>>Enum_List 
84803>>>>>>>>>>>    Define DF_ASCII_DUF     for 1500
84803>>>>>>>>>>>    Define DF_BCD_DUF       for 1499
84803>>>>>>>>>>>    Define DF_BINARY_DUF    for 1494
84803>>>>>>>>>>>    Define DF_DATE_DUF      for 1498
84803>>>>>>>>>>>    Define DF_DATETIME_DUF  for 1493
84803>>>>>>>>>>>    Define DF_TEXT_DUF      for 1495
84803>>>>>>>>>>>End_Enum_List
84803>>>>>>>>>>>
84803>>>>>>>>>>>Define CS_DbTypeMSSQL       for "Microsoft SQL Server"
84803>>>>>>>>>>>Define CS_DbTypeMySQL       for "MySQL"
84803>>>>>>>>>>>Define CS_DbTypeOracle      for "Oracle"
84803>>>>>>>>>>>Define CS_DbTypeDB2         for "IBM DB2"
84803>>>>>>>>>>>Define CS_DbTypePostgre     for "PostgreSQL"
84803>>>>>>>>>>>Define CS_DbTypeDataFlex    for "DataFlex Embedded"
84803>>>>>>>>>>>
84803>>>>>>>>>>>    Define SQL_TEXT for (DF_TEXT + 1024)
84803>>>>>>>>>>>
84803>>>>>>>>>>>Define SQL_CHARBIT          for (DF_BINARY + 1024)
84803>>>>>>>>>>>Define SQL_LONGVARCHARBIT   for (DF_BINARY + 1025)
84803>>>>>>>>>>>Define SQL_VARCHARBIT       for (DF_BINARY + 1026)
