Including file: StatusPanel.pkg    (C:\Projects\DF18\DbUpdateFramework\AppSrc\StatusPanel.pkg)
87048>>>>>// StatPnl.pkg - creates the standard status_panel object.
87048>>>>>//
87048>>>>>//
87048>>>>>// This is the default Status Panel object used by any of the Visual DataFlex classes that
87048>>>>>// invoke the standard status panel. The standard has always been that the package name
87048>>>>>// is StatPnl.pkg and the name of the object is Status_Panel. As of 12.0, there are major
87048>>>>>// changes in the way the status panel operates The Sentinel based external status panel used in
87048>>>>>// prior revisions has been replace with status panel that is part of the application.
87048>>>>>// This should work much better and faster than the old sentinel based solution.
87048>>>>>// While the way this operates has changed, the interface has not and therefore this should work
87048>>>>>// with most applications.
87048>>>>>//
87048>>>>>// As of 12.0, we have added a global handle that contains the object ID of this status panel.
87048>>>>>// This variable ghoStatusPanel can be used in place of the object name Status_Panel. This provides
87048>>>>>// a cleaner more robust interface.
87048>>>>>//
87048>>>>>//
87048>>>>>// Compatibility Note:
87048>>>>>//
87048>>>>>// When used in the standard way, this change will require no changes. A developer will only need to
87048>>>>>// change their code if they've modified the sentinel program, which was a difficult thing to do.
87048>>>>>//
87048>>>>>// If for some reason you application will not work using this as a replacement for the old status
87048>>>>>// panel, you've probably done something special with the old status-panel. If you don't want to
87048>>>>>// figure out how to use the new one and you want to continue using the old one you are going to need
87048>>>>>// to add some code to include the old status panel in your application. Add the following to your project (your src).
87048>>>>>//
87048>>>>>// Use StatPnl.pkg    // Make sure you load the new status panel object first. this is not optional!
87048>>>>>// Use OldStatPnl.pkg // load the old status panel. Status_Panel is now this old object
87048>>>>>//
87048>>>>>// If you do this, you will lose access to the new status-panel via Status_Panel. However, you
87048>>>>>// can still access the new object via the ghoStatusPanel handle.
87048>>>>>//
87048>>>>>//
87048>>>>>// Creating your own Status Panel objects
87048>>>>>//
87048>>>>>// If a developer wishes to create a custom panel, they should use this package as their template.
87048>>>>>// This panel can be visually modeled and changed any way you wish. Just save your new custom panel
87048>>>>>// with a different file and object name and direct your status panel request to the new object.
87048>>>>>//
87048>>>>>// If the new panel changes the interface and updates objects that are not currently defined, you
87048>>>>>// want to make sure you send the message ProcessEvents after you've updated the object. This allows
87048>>>>>// the object to paint when inside of a tight loop. For example, if you wanted to add a progress
87048>>>>>// bar (cProgressBar) you would want to Send ProcessEvents after you update the progress bar.
87048>>>>>// e.g.
87048>>>>>//       Procedure UpdateStatusBar
87048>>>>>//           Send DoAdvance of oProgressBar
87048>>>>>//           Send ProcessEvents
87048>>>>>//       End_Procedure
87048>>>>>//
87048>>>>>// of course, if you use the standard interfaces in status bar and your forward send these
87048>>>>>// messages this will be done for you.
87048>>>>>//
87048>>>>>// the standard Interface for status panels are:
87048>>>>>//
87048>>>>>// Send Initialize_StatusPanel - initializes values for caption, title & message
87048>>>>>// Send Start_StatusPanel      - start the status panel
87048>>>>>// Send Stop_StatusPanel       - stop the status panel
87048>>>>>// Send Update_StatusPanel     - update the status panel's action area
87048>>>>>// Get  Check_StatusPanel      - check for cancel (if cancel or pbCancel is set, close the panel)
87048>>>>>//
87048>>>>>// Get/Set Caption_Text - updates the caption bar
87048>>>>>// Get/Set Title_Text   - updates the title area
87048>>>>>// Get/Set Message_Text - updates the Message area
87048>>>>>// Get/Set Action_Text  - updates the action area
87048>>>>>// Get/Set Button_Text  - updates the button area
87048>>>>>//
87048>>>>>// Get/Set Allow_cancel_state - determines if panel can be canceled
87048>>>>>// Send EnableCancelButton - code you should provide to enable/disable cancel button
87048>>>>>//
87048>>>>>// ghoStatusPanel - global handle that points to the standard status panel.
87048>>>>>Use cProcessStatusPanel.pkg
87048>>>>>Use cCJSkinFramework.pkg
87048>>>>>//Use cAnimation.pkg
87048>>>>>Use cProgressBar.pkg
