94109>>>    // Returns the handle of the Mertech SQL handler.
94109>>>    // It also ensures that the correct Server & Database attributes are set both for 
94109>>>    // embedded SQL calls and "normal" database commands like e.g. "Open".
94109>>>    Function _MertechSQLManagerHandle Returns Handle
94111>>>        Handle hoSQLHandler
94111>>>        String sDriverID sServer sDatabase
94111>>>        
94111>>>        Move 0 to hoSQLHandler
94112>>>        Get psDriverID to sDriverID       
94113>>>        Get psServer   to sServer
94114>>>        Get psDatabase to sDatabase
94115>>>        // This command is used to set the server to be used when opening tables   
94115>>>        SET_CURRENT_SQL_SERVER            to sServer  
94134>>>>
94134>>>        // This command is used to specify which server to use for embedded SQL statements,
94134>>>        // but it has been constructed rather studidly as only constants and not variables
94134>>>        // are allowed...
94134>>>        If (sDriverID = MDSPgSQL) Begin
94136>>>            SET_CURRENT_SQL_SERVER_CONNECTION of MDSPgSQL to sServer
94152>>>        End
94152>>>>
94152>>>        If (sDriverID = MDSMySQL) Begin
94154>>>            SET_CURRENT_SQL_SERVER_CONNECTION of MDSMySQL to sServer
94170>>>        End
94170>>>>
94170>>>        If (sDriverID = ORAFLEX) Begin
94172>>>            SET_CURRENT_SQL_SERVER_CONNECTION of ORAFLEX to sServer
94188>>>        End
94188>>>>
94188>>>        If (sDriverID = SQLFLEX) Begin
94190>>>            SET_CURRENT_SQL_SERVER_CONNECTION of SQLFLEX to sServer
94206>>>        End
94206>>>>
94206>>>        
94206>>>        // This command is used to specify which database is used for SQL statements only.
94206>>>        SQL_USE_DATABASE sDatabase
94220>>>>
94220>>>        SET_DATABASE_NAME to sDatabase
94234>>>>
94234>>>        
94234>>>        Get phoSQLManagerMT to hoSQLHandler  
94235>>>        
94235>>>        Function_Return hoSQLHandler
94236>>>    End_Function
