94465>>>
94465>>>// This provides a quick and simple way to create an about package for a program.
94465>>>// You need to create a message inside you client area called Activate_About.
94465>>>// Within this message you should send the message DoAbout passing needed
94465>>>// string information.
94465>>>//
94465>>>//       Procedure Activate_About
94465>>>//           Send DoAbout sTitle sVersion sCopyright sAuthor sBitmap
94465>>>//       End_Procedure
94465>>>//    where: sTitle =     Name of application. If none provided, uses caption
94465>>>//                        bar title
94465>>>//           sVersion   = Version Line. If none provided, will be blank
94465>>>//           sCopyRight = Copyright Line. If none provided, will be blank
94465>>>//           sAuthor    = Author name, blank if none provided
94465>>>//           sBitMap    = Bitmap logo. If none provided, standard VDF bitmap
94465>>>//                        is used.
94465>>>// It is expected that you will place this in your own object package. For
94465>>>// example an order about package may look like this:
94465>>>//
94465>>>//   // OrderAbout.pkg
94465>>>//   Use StdAbout.pkg
94465>>>//   Procedure Activate_About
94465>>>//      String sTitle sCopyright sVersion sAuthor
94465>>>//      Move "My Order Entry System" to sTitle
94465>>>//      Move "Version 2.1" to sVersion
94465>>>//      Move "Copyright 1997, Super Software Inc." to sCopyright
94465>>>//      Move "John Smith"  to sAuthor
94465>>>//      Send DoAbout sTitle sVersion sCopyright sAuthor ""
94465>>>//   end_procedure
94465>>>//   // end of file.
94465>>>
94465>>>Use DfAbout.pkg
Including file: DfAbout.pkg    (C:\Projects\DF18\DbUpdateFramework\AppSrc\DfAbout.pkg)
