94751>>>>>>>>>>>
94751>>>>>>>>>>>// Help System Package
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//
94751>>>>>>>>>>>// Public Properties that should be set:
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//     Property String  Help_Filename   (Help_File_Default(self))
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//     Property Integer Help_Id_General 0
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//     Property Integer Help_Id_Index   0
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//     Property Integer Help_Id_Keys    0
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//     Property Integer Help_Id_Files   0
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//     Property Integer Help_Id_Errors  0
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//
94751>>>>>>>>>>>// Public messsages which are sent to this object:
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Context_KeyWord_Help integer Obj
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Context_ID_Help      integer Obj
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Context_Help         integer Obj
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Help_for_help        integer Obj
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_help_index           integer Obj
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Keys_Help            integer Obj
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_File_Help            integer Obj
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Error_Help           integer Obj
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Help_on_Topic        integer Obj
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//
94751>>>>>>>>>>>// Protected Messages:
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//        These messages invoke the Window's help system and are not
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//        directly sent by outside objects. They are sent by public
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//        "view_xxx" messages and might be used if you are creating
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//        a sub-class of an object-class.
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//    Procedure Exec_System_Context_Help  integer Context_id
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//    Procedure Exec_System_Help          string  Keyword
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//    Procedure Exec_Context_Help         string  Context
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//    Functions for converting DF help IDs to windows Help Ids
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//        Any of these can return either a string or an integer.
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//    Function System_Help_Context_id Integer ID Returns String
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//           Convert a DF help context id into a windows id. By default,
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//           just return the same value (a one to one match). This is called
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//           by View_Context_id_help and View_Context_Help
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//    Function System_Help_File_Id Integer File# Integer Field# Returns String
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//           Convert file and field into a help id. By default it returns the
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//           file#. Called by View_File_Help.
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//    Function System_Help_Error_id Integer Id Returns String
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//           Convert an error message into an ID. Right now it returns the
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//           the general error context id property, Help_id_errors. This
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//           will invoke general error help. If you want error support at the
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//           error# level you will have to determine the program to help
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//           interface yourself. Errors have a very large range and it is
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//           therefore hard to come up with an automatic numbering scheme.
94751>>>>>>>>>>>//           Called by View_Error_Help.
94751>>>>>>>>>>>
94751>>>>>>>>>>>
94751>>>>>>>>>>>Use Windows.pkg
94751>>>>>>>>>>>Use WinHlp.pkg // low level help call to windows API provides global message gDoWinHelp
94751>>>>>>>>>>>Use HelpSystemConstants.pkg // constants used by help system
94751>>>>>>>>>>>
94751>>>>>>>>>>>Register_Function phoWorkspace Returns Handle
94751>>>>>>>>>>>Register_function peHelpType  returns integer
94751>>>>>>>>>>>
94751>>>>>>>>>>>class HelpSystem is an cObject
94752>>>>>>>>>>>
94752>>>>>>>>>>>    register_function Help_File_Default returns string
94752>>>>>>>>>>>
94752>>>>>>>>>>>    procedure Construct_Object
94754>>>>>>>>>>>       Forward send Construct_Object
94756>>>>>>>>>>>
94756>>>>>>>>>>>       // Help file name only. If set, this overrides all other settings.
94756>>>>>>>>>>>       Property String psHelpFile
94757>>>>>>>>>>>
94757>>>>>>>>>>>       // Help_FileName
94757>>>>>>>>>>>       //   full path name of Help file. The default value grabs its value
94757>>>>>>>>>>>       //   from .ini or environment settings. See functiob Help_file_Default
94757>>>>>>>>>>>       //
94757>>>>>>>>>>>       Property String  Private.Help_Filename (Help_File_Default(self))
94758>>>>>>>>>>>
94758>>>>>>>>>>>       // The following properties are the default values for the help files
94758>>>>>>>>>>>       // IDs for the various subjects. Setting these requires an agreement
94758>>>>>>>>>>>       // between the DF help system and the help file.
94758>>>>>>>>>>>       //
94758>>>>>>>>>>>       Property Integer Help_Id_General  0
94759>>>>>>>>>>>       Property Integer Help_Id_Index    0
94760>>>>>>>>>>>       Property Integer Help_Id_Keys     0
94761>>>>>>>>>>>       Property Integer Help_Id_Files    0
94762>>>>>>>>>>>       Property Integer Help_Id_Errors   0
94763>>>>>>>>>>>
94763>>>>>>>>>>>       // this is now the default help object
94763>>>>>>>>>>>       Move self to Help_Object_id
94764>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Procedure
94765>>>>>>>>>>>
94765>>>>>>>>>>>   // New rules for VDF8:
94765>>>>>>>>>>>   // 1. If psHelpFile exists, find the file in the file path and use it
94765>>>>>>>>>>>   // 2. If application object exists and help type is windows, use psHelpFile from there, find in file path and use it.
94765>>>>>>>>>>>   // 3. If no help file exists, use thge old private help name (which gets the full name from the registry -only if no app object)
94765>>>>>>>>>>>   //    Last method is deprecated and only used for old applications
94765>>>>>>>>>>>   //
94765>>>>>>>>>>>   Function Help_filename returns string
94767>>>>>>>>>>>        string sHelpName
94767>>>>>>>>>>>        // If ghoWorkSpace Get Help_FileName of ghoWorkSpace to sHelpName // removed for VDF8
94767>>>>>>>>>>>
94767>>>>>>>>>>>        // If an Application object is used, take the name from there.
94767>>>>>>>>>>>        Get psHelpFile to sHelpName
94768>>>>>>>>>>>        If (sHelpName="" AND ghoApplication AND peHelpType(ghoApplication)=htWinHelp) Begin
94770>>>>>>>>>>>            Get psHelpFile of ghoApplication To sHelpName
94771>>>>>>>>>>>            //Move (psHelpPath(phoWorkspace(ghoApplication)) -"\" -sHelpName) To sHelpName
94771>>>>>>>>>>>        End
94771>>>>>>>>>>>>
94771>>>>>>>>>>>        If (sHelpName<>"") begin
94773>>>>>>>>>>>            Get_File_Path sHelpName To sHelpName
94774>>>>>>>>>>>            Function_Return sHelpName
94775>>>>>>>>>>>        end
94775>>>>>>>>>>>>
94775>>>>>>>>>>>        // if not set anywhere (and ideally it is) we use this.
94775>>>>>>>>>>>        Get Private.Help_FileName to sHelpName
94776>>>>>>>>>>>        Function_Return sHelpName
94777>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function
94778>>>>>>>>>>>
94778>>>>>>>>>>>    Procedure Set Help_FileName string sName
94780>>>>>>>>>>>        Set Private.Help_FileName to sName
94781>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Procedure
94782>>>>>>>>>>>
94782>>>>>>>>>>>
94782>>>>>>>>>>>
94782>>>>>>>>>>>    // Consider this message PRIVATE in that it should only be changed
94782>>>>>>>>>>>    // by a sub-class and not an object. It is called in construct_object
94782>>>>>>>>>>>    // before it knows about object augmentations!!!!
94782>>>>>>>>>>>    //
94782>>>>>>>>>>>    //  Sets the Help_file_name by looking at the .INI file for:
94782>>>>>>>>>>>    //        HELP_DIR    - help directory (will check environment variable
94782>>>>>>>>>>>    //                      windir if not found - avoid this usage). If not
94782>>>>>>>>>>>    //                      blank append "\" as required.
94782>>>>>>>>>>>    //
94782>>>>>>>>>>>    //        HELP_FILE   - help file name. If blank uses the default help
94782>>>>>>>>>>>    //                      file name
94782>>>>>>>>>>>    //
94782>>>>>>>>>>>    Function Help_File_Default Returns String
94784>>>>>>>>>>>       String HelpFileDir HelpFileName sSubKey
94784>>>>>>>>>>>       // if using the application object we expect the help name to be
94784>>>>>>>>>>>       // defined in the application object or directly in the help object. No Exceptions
94784>>>>>>>>>>>       If (ghoApplication) function_return ""
94787>>>>>>>>>>>
94787>>>>>>>>>>>       // else if no application (and hence no WS) use an old deprecated method of checking
94787>>>>>>>>>>>       // for the module name in local_machine.
94787>>>>>>>>>>>       Get Module_name of Desktop to sSubKey
94788>>>>>>>>>>>       Get_Profile_String sSubKey HELP_DIR to HelpFileDir
94791>>>>>>>>>>>       Get_Profile_String sSubKey HELP_FILE to HelpFileName
94794>>>>>>>>>>>       // if dir exists, sure it has a "\" at the end. If no directory the
94794>>>>>>>>>>>       // dir must be blank so current directory is searched
94794>>>>>>>>>>>       If ( (HelpFileDir<>'') AND (Right(HelpFileDir,1)<>"\") ) ;          Move (HelpFileDir - '\') to HelpFileDir
94797>>>>>>>>>>>       If HelpFileName eq '' Move DEFAULT_HELP_FILENAME to HelpFileName
94800>>>>>>>>>>>       Function_Return (HelpFileDir - HelpFileName)
94801>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function
94802>>>>>>>>>>>
94802>>>>>>>>>>>    // The System_Help_xxxx messages convert a DF help integer ID into
94802>>>>>>>>>>>    // a context value that can be used by the windows help system. If
94802>>>>>>>>>>>    // you return a number or a string. Numbers will get used for context ID
94802>>>>>>>>>>>    // help, non-numbers get used for keyword context help
94802>>>>>>>>>>>
94802>>>>>>>>>>>    // By default return ID passed. This creates a direct mapping between
94802>>>>>>>>>>>    // context IDs in your object and the context IDs in windows help.
94802>>>>>>>>>>>    //
94802>>>>>>>>>>>    Function System_Help_Context_id Integer ID Returns String
94804>>>>>>>>>>>       Function_Return ID
94805>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function // System_Help_Context_id
94806>>>>>>>>>>>
94806>>>>>>>>>>>    // Returns the file# which assumes that we have a direct mapping between
94806>>>>>>>>>>>    // the file number and a window's help context_id. We are ignoring field#
94806>>>>>>>>>>>    // in this case (although your augmentation would not have to). If the
94806>>>>>>>>>>>    // file# is 0, return a the HELP_ID context id.
94806>>>>>>>>>>>    //
94806>>>>>>>>>>>    Function System_Help_File_Id Integer File# Integer Field# Returns String
94808>>>>>>>>>>>       String rVal
94808>>>>>>>>>>>       if File# eq 0 Move (Help_id_files(self)) to rVal
94811>>>>>>>>>>>       Else Move File# to rVal
94813>>>>>>>>>>>       Function_Return Rval
94814>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function // System_Help_File_id
94815>>>>>>>>>>>
94815>>>>>>>>>>>    // Convert an error id into a help context id. Return the general
94815>>>>>>>>>>>    // Help id property value. We do this because error number have
94815>>>>>>>>>>>    // a rather large range (1-9000) and just using the number would consume
94815>>>>>>>>>>>    // too much of the context id space.
94815>>>>>>>>>>>    //
94815>>>>>>>>>>>    Function System_Help_Error_id Integer Id Returns String
94817>>>>>>>>>>>       Function_Return (Help_Id_Errors(self))
94818>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function // System_Help_Error_id
94819>>>>>>>>>>>
94819>>>>>>>>>>>    // Use this if you want your help context to be keyword based
